I understood your question but use `break` statement to go out of loops like `for`, `while`, `do while`. You can go out of `if` statement when the condition is satisfied and statements inside the `if` branch are executed. If you don&#39;t want to check for other conditions when your first `if` is satisfied you have to use `if else` branches instead of using 4 if statements.
